### Description

Hello, I apologize if this question is not entirely relevant to this place, but as for me, the ideological nature of this option would be nice

After the migration of Angular 17 to vite, I encountered a problem that it was not possible to merge all new files into one single file without changing the builder to the old one `@angular-devkit/build-angular:browser`

I have already encountered a similar problem before, but the methods described in this problem do not work at all
https://github.com/angular/angular-cli/issues/3288

Unfortunately, instead of using the new builder with vite, you have to switch to the old one @angular-devkit/build-angular:browser
In this case, I use the following script file to assemble all the files into one:

```
const fs = require("fs-extra");
const concat = require("concat");

const componentPath = "./dist/build/bundle.js";

(async function build() {
    const files = [
        "./dist/angular-app/main.js",
        "./dist/angular-app/polyfills.js"
    ].filter(x => fs.pathExistsSync(x));
    await fs.ensureFile(componentPath);
    await concat(files, componentPath);
})();
```

What steps can I take now to solve my problem?

